Bedroom

You are in a small bedroom that looks like it was repurposed from a study. There is a bed with pink covers, a desk, a chair, and barely enough room left to stand. A bookshelf in the corner is packed full from row to row, with some books jammed in horizontally to make optimal use of the available space. The afternoon sun streams in from a small window. A doorway to the North leads into the hallway, but curiously there is no door in the frame.

The house came with a door, obviously, but her mother took it out. Privacy is not an idea that Asian parents believe in.

You can see a calendar, a bed, a chair, a bookshelf and a desk.
