Rainy Street

You find yourself on the streets of a small town. You can see a library, a cafe, and a couple of shops. In front of you is a boarded up office, with a banner that reads "ACE Tutoring Agency". There is a light drizzle and the rain lends the pavement a silvery shine.

You can see a notice, a picket sign and a newspaper clipping.
> read newspaper clipping

> read newspaper clipping
The clipping of "The Medicine Hat Chronicles" is attached to the door with duct tape.

John Hubert, 27, has been sentenced to life in prison today for the murder of Jenny Lee. The body of the 17  year old was found on the morning of May 9th in the grounds of Central Park, a 20 minute walk from her home. Her head had been bashed in with her own saxophone, the impact so great that the keys were knocked clean off. The sensational trial, which lasted three weeks, was cinched in the end by irrefutable physical evidence. Traces of semen that were found in Lee's dress have been matched to Hubert's DNA.

Hubert has been a resident of Medicine Hat for 10 years; previously he resided in Ottawa, where he was born. He worked as a tutor at the ACE Tutoring Agency, where one of his students was Jenny Lee . . .

Ah. So you've found it. My secret.

Should I be angry? Disappointed? Ashamed?

Who are you to judge me? You're just a computer program. You don't know what it's like to love. And I did love her. She was so beautiful, so different from all the other girls I taught, so different from the girls I've dated in the past. There was something special about her, something I'll never see again . . .

I admit I have reason for shame. She was only 17. But what happened on that last day, in her bedroom . . . that was consensual. I would never have raised a finger to hurt her.

The last detective was the same. Prying into things that didn't concern him, always asking the wrong questions. In the end, I had to deactivate him. Well, are you happy now? To tell the truth, I couldn't care less what you think. I'll just get another one after you're gone. But since you've gotten this far . . . I'll give you one last chance. One more hour to find the real killer. And then it's lights off for you. Well, what are you waiting for? I wouldn't waste any time if I were you.

