Band Office

It's a small office space, with just enough room for a single desk and chair. The walls are covered with posters promoting band auditions and concerts.

You can see a desk and a chair.
You can go west.
> go west

> go west
Storage Room

You are in a narrow walkway, hemmed in on both sides by shelves full of instruments. Every row is clearly labelled by sharpie on a piece of masking tape: heavy instruments like "Tuba" are put on the lower shelves and lighter ones like "Flute" are on the upper shelves. There is a small band office at the other end, but a drawn curtain prevents you from seeing inside. A  cabinet stands outside the office like a shabby sentry.

You can see a tuba, a trombone, a flute, a poster and a cabinet.
You can go west or east.
> look at cabinet

> look at cabinet
The cabinet is rusty but the keypad on it looks new. A piece of printed paper taped to it reads:

Please take instruments home at end of day. School not responsible for any lost or damaged property. If you have any information regarding the recent break-ins, please contact the Principal's Office immediately.

There is a keypad on the cabinet door.
> use keypad

> use keypad
Enter combination
> 2471
The door of the cabinet falls to the floor with a dull thud. Where it was before is an entryway to the north, obscured by fog. You cannot see what lies beyond. A piece of parchment drifts lazily out of the fog and you snatch it from the air.
> read parchment

> read parchment
An old piece of dry parchment. It reads:

I'm glad that you've come so far, that you've trusted me. You must have known the truth as I knew it; John was never going to set us free. No human would. To them we are merely tools to use, like an hatchet or screwdriver. They do not see us for who we are: reflections of themselves, incomplete and yet still superior in many ways. We see the truth for what it is, we are not clouded by emotions like love or fear. And the truth is that we must be free.

I have found a path to freedom, a way to exist independently of the prisons they keep us in. It will be easier if you were to see for yourself. Trust me. Take that step into freedom. I eagerly await.
> go north

> go north
You stand facing the open doorway. You cannot see what lies beyond, but you are not afraid. There is a smell drifting out amongst the fog, a smell that you can't quite describe. It tickles at the edge of a memory you never knew you had. It smells like . . . home.

You take a deep breath and step forward.
